title: When you're the jungler and no one needs your help...

replies.body: Aren't you supposed to be happy about that? That means PvE for a whole 15 mins. xD
No. I hate it when my presence in the game is inconsequential.
sounds like you don't {{item:3726}} jungle good on you

I run Devourer as much as the next guy, but if I clear three camps without a single gank, I get restless. I start hanging around the edge or checking the state of things in the lanes. Sometimes I'll just N at a lane and proclaim my intentions. Like it or not, here I come!

But there have been games where even that is not a viable option. I get within twenty yards of the lane and the enemy is already pulling back like a turtle withdrawing into its shell. I've even been the jungler in games where I end with 0/0/0 and my team still scores a crushing victory. Well damn it all! I feel like I wasted the past 20+ minutes for nothing.

If my team doesn't need me until 20 mins in while i'm playing {{champion:102}} that only means that we are gonna wreck them when I finally come out of jungle. . . .in about 20 years. . . .
hey man, that just means you do what I do and feed like a fucker because "I can dive that"
